Exploratory analyses summer 2017

We collected a lot of data this past summer which are creating more questions than answers. Here are the highlights of analyses so far. For more see the Figures folder in the Seagrass 2017 sections of the APECS-ak GitHub repository. I also hope that this summary document helps convince everyone (especially people that will be running lots of analyses) that things like RMarkdown and GitHUb are really useful for a collaborative project.

Where we worked

We covered a lot of gorund this past summer

Sea otters

Our primary questions for this part of the APECS project what effect, if any, do sea otters have in eelgrass ecosystems in Southeast Alaska. To get at this we have compared many of our response metrics to our sea otter index. Since we only sampled sites once we are also concerned that time is an important factor to keep control of. So the following set of plots will present the sea otter index and time for comparison.

The sea otter index is a number or score assigned to each of our sites that combines our boat based sea otter surveys, calm and pit survey, known sea otter duration, and population model desity estimates. This was done using a PCA and is plotted below.
